<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="177" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1823,2028]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,752]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="177" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1823,1848]" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">Description</emphasis>
. Male (
<figureCitation box="[423,491,1823,1848]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1070,1092]" captionTargetBox="[232,1357,347,1025]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[225,1362,337,1049]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 9. Loboschiza flavobasis n. sp., male holotype (9 mm wingspan), Vietnam." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262535/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[512,573,1823,1848]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[587,724,1823,1848]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1761,1784]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,1142,1740]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[217,1369,1142,1740]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 11. Loboschiza flavobasis n. sp., male, head (lateral and dorsal views)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262536/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">Figs. 10–11</figureCitation>
): Vertex light yellow; frons white; labial palpus white basally to middle of segment II, then brown, gradually becoming light yellow distally, with mesal side light yellow; antenna yellow on basal 1/4, then pale tan. 
<emphasis box="[568,649,1895,1920]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">Thorax</emphasis>
: Dorsum brown, margined with yellow on tegulae; patagia yellow; venter cream-white. Legs cream-white on coxae and femur; foretibia dark gray on dorsal edge; midtibia tan-yellow, with 2 rings of gray-brown; hindtibia gray on dorsal edge; mesally all legs pale tan; fore- and mid-tarsi light tan with dark gray distally on each segment; hind-tarsi gray with light tan on distal margin of each segment. Wingspan 9.0 mm (n = 1); forewing mostly yellow, with outer 1/3 dark brown, overlain with several curved and irregular pale brown striae from costal margin to tornus; fringe dark brown; venter gray-tan with few dark gray spots on apical 1/ 4 and some gray strigulae on costal margin. Hindwing dark brown; fringe concolorous with wing; venter gray, with tan-gray costal margin. 
<emphasis box="[422,528,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="177">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Dark brown, brown-yellow on tergite 2; venter dull cream-white; genital tufts tan and ventrally gray-white; sternal pregenital plate a sharply pointed triangle; anterior of abdomen lacking interapodemal fan-shaped arrangement of spines, but with small spines along the inter-apodeme margins and a long setal coremata from near each apodeme. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[815,900,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1968,1990]" captionTargetBox="[158,1435,812,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,805,1946]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 12. Loboschiza flavobasis n. sp., male genitalia (aedeagus in situ). a) central area of genitalia; b) anterior of abdomen (ventral view); and c) pregenital sternal plate (genitalia slide JBH 3375)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262537/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="177">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) with tegumen triangular, narrowed dorsally, lacking uncus; socius laterally setose and fold-like, and extended dorsally as pair of extended setose, short projections; vinculum with reduced to sharply rounded saccus; valva short, angled dorsally and setose, uniform in width in basal one-half (to the outer 1/2), with dorsal bulbous margin; sacculus a small quadrate setose exvagination, while rest of saccular margin nearly straight, with small apical hook on pointed cucullus; juxta somewhat tubular, short, with lateral flat but carinate sides; anellus a short dorsally open tube, slightly bent; aedeagus long and thin (subequal in length to valva), with dense patch of deciduous long and lanceolate cornuti (ca. 60).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,752]" box="[199,414,655,680]" pageId="6" pageNumber="177">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
