<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="178" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,392]" pageId="7" pageNumber="178">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,260,285]" pageId="7" pageNumber="178">Discussion</emphasis>
. The genitalia of the new species are somewhat similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyrick" authorityName="Meyrick" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Loboschiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exemplaris">
<emphasis box="[1171,1436,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="178">Loboschiza exemplaris</emphasis>
(Meyrick)
</taxonomicName>
from northern 
<collectingCountry box="[437,543,295,320]" name="Australia" pageId="7" pageNumber="178">Australia</collectingCountry>
, but the forewing maculation is quite different. This species is known from the single specimen from Ba Be Park in northern 
<collectingCountry box="[664,762,332,357]" name="Vietnam" pageId="7" pageNumber="178">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, similar to many species in the genus which are known only from singletons, as noted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Horak" box="[474,629,367,392]" pageId="7" pageNumber="178" refString="Horak, M. (2006) Olethreutine Moths of Australia (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae). Monographs on Australian Lepidoptera 10. CSIRO, Collingwood, 528 pp." type="book" year="2006">Horak (2006)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
